hdiutil resize: resize partition or image
Usage:	hdiutil resize <sizespec> <image>
	Size specifiers:
	    -size < ?? | ??b | ??k | ??m | ??g | ??t | ??p | ??e | min | max >
	        (bytes, blocks, kilobytes, megabytes, gigabytes, terabytes, petabytes, exabytes)
	    -sectors <sector count>
		min		minimum size
		max		maximum size

	Resize options:
	    -imageonly		only change image file size
	    -partitiononly	only change the partition size
	    -partitionNumber <#> resize given partition [last]
	    -limits		for given options, print min/current/max sizes
	    -growonly		only allow image to grow
	    -shrinkonly		only allow image to shrink
	    -nofinalgap		allow elimination of trailing free partition

	Common options:
	    -encryption <crypto method>
	    -stdinpass
	    -srcimagekey <key>=<value>	(-imagekey is a synonym)
	    -shadow <shadowfile>
	    -insecurehttp
	    -cacert <file|dir>
	    -plist			return results in plist format
	    -verbose
	    -debug
	    -quiet
